A UE can be configured with a list of up to M transmission configuration indicator (TCI)-State configurations within the higher layer parameter PDSCH-Config to receive PDSCH in a serving cell where M depends on the UE capability maxNumberConfiguredTClstatesPerCC. Each TCI-State contains parameters for configuring a QCL relationship between one or two downlink reference signals and the DMRS ports of the PDSCH, the DMRS port of a corresponding PDCCH, or the CSI-RS port(s) of a CSI-RS resource. The quasi co-location relationship is configured by the higher layer parameter qcl-Type1 for the first DL RS, and qcl-Type2 for the second DL RS (if configured). For the case of two DL RSs, the QCL types shall not be the same, regardless of whether the references are to the same DL RS or different DL RSs. The quasi co-location types corresponding to each DL RS are given by the higher layer parameter qcl-Type in QCL-Info and may take one of the following values:


- - ‘QCL-TypeA’: {Doppler shift, Doppler spread, average delay, delay
    spread}
  - ‘QCL-TypeB’: {Doppler shift, Doppler spread}
  - ‘QCL-TypeC’: {Doppler shift, average delay}
  - ‘QCL-TypeD’: {Spatial Rx parameter}

